<br>
The first monk I made, got him to lvl 28, he had some good gear for that time, this was back when I was still had tons to learn about EQ.  I discovered druids and lost interest in the monk at that time, got my druid to lvl 51 eventually, but druid is just my utility char now, haven't exp'd with him in months.<br>
<br>
I spent a lot of plat twinking my recent monk (like 75% of my funds at least), thinking it was a wise investment, drooling over someday getting my epic (a large part of why I twinked so hard, wanted the epic sooooooooo bad, and I didn't want to wait =P), then I was virtually crushed when just at the peak of enjoying my monk, at lvl 48, after just camping and killing Raster, I get the news they're gonna gimp my new pride and joy.<br>
<br>
So for now my monk is on the shelf, since the reason I made him, mainly cuz I figured I could solo well into my 50's, specially with epic, was just thrown out the window.  You buy a sports car cuz it hauls ass, then the Government decides it's too dangerous, and puts a speed cap on it, you'd lose interest too.  I'm not a roleplayer, more of a power gamer I guess, I like kicking butt, but I like a challenge too.  I felt challenged with my monk, even with a fungi, IFS, 31% haste, really nice gear, just shy of 1000AC at lvl 48.  Course I had the obvious edge over monks with lesser gear, but I did not at all feel &quot;all powerful&quot; or unstoppable, I still had to use feign death to save my butt sometimes, etc, being overpowered never entered my mind, and I've played MANY characters to lvl 40+, to compare my power to. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskewert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skewert</A> at: 10/17/02 2:39:04 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showPrevMessage?topicID=386.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showNextMessage?topicID=386.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.emailToFriend?topicID=386.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.threadControl?topicID=386.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif borde